  h2.ui.dividing.header
    a.link(href="http://libocca.org") OCCA
  a(href="http://libocca.org")
    img(src="/images/projects/occa/occaFlow.png" style="display: block; max-width: 700px; width: 100%; height: auto; margin: auto;")
  .indent1
    div(style="line-height: 20px")
      br
    +highlight('OCCA')
    | &nbsp;is an open-source (
    +highlight('MIT license')
    | ) library used to program current multi-core/many-core architectures.
    | Devices (such as&nbsp;
    +highlight2('CPUs, GPUs, Intel\'s Xeon Phi, FPGAs')
    | , etc) are abstracted using an offload-model for application development and programming for the devices is done through a C-based (
    +highlight('OKL')
    | ) or Fortran-based kernel language (
    +highlight('OFL')
    | ).
    | OCCA gives developers the ability to target devices at run-time by using run-time compilation for device kernels.

